{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881544430,"sessionID":"ses_2853666dbffeDUJW2TNchl5Tol","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac9d81a001PopOfG4lH4s13C","messageID":"msg_d7ac9cb5d001o5r6Lex2MABFWq","sessionID":"ses_2853666dbffeDUJW2TNchl5Tol","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 (Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller)\n2: \n3: > **Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n4: > **Language:** Go  \n5: > **Size:** S  \n6: > **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n7: > **Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md), idle-cleanup/design.md\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: AR-018 implements the Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller that watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). The controller uses controller-runtime for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-4.1 — Package Structure and Constants\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 4.1.1 | Create `pkg/agentd/` directory structure | Directory exists | 0.25h |\n22: | 4.1.2 | Create `pkg/agentd/reconciler.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n23: | 4.1.3 | Define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute` constant | Constant defined and exported | 0.25h |\n24: | 4.1.4 | Define `RequeueAfterParseError = 30 * time.Second` constant | Constant defined and exported | 0.25h |\n25: | 4.1.5 | Add package-level doc comment | `go doc ./pkg/agentd` shows overview | 0.25h |\n26: \n27: **Deliverable:** Package structure compiles with constants defined.\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## ST-4.2 — Reconciler Struct and Interface\n32: \n33: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n34: |---|------|--------------|------|\n35: | 4.2.1 | Define `Reconciler` struct with `client.Client` and `Scheme *runtime.Scheme` fields | Struct matches delta-spec | 0.5h |\n36: | 4.2.2 | Import required packages (`sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client`, `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime`) | All imports resolve | 0.25h |\n37: | 4.2.3 | Import `workloadmanager` package for annotation key constant | Import path correct | 0.25h |\n38: | 4.2.4 | Import Sandbox types from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1` | Type references compile | 0.5h |\n39: \n40: **Deliverable:** Reconciler struct defined with correct fields and imports.\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## ST-4.3 — Reconcile Method Implementation\n45: \n46: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n47: |---|------|--------------|------|\n48: | 4.3.1 | Implement `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)` signature | Method signature matches spec | 0.25h |\n49: | 4.3.2 | Fetch Sandbox: `sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}`; `r.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)` | Get call compiles | 0.5h |\n50: | 4.3.3 | Handle `IsNotFound` error from Get: return `ctrl.Result{}, nil` | NotFound returns empty result | 0.5h |\n51: | 4.3.4 | Handle other Get errors: return `ctrl.Result{}, err` | Other errors returned | 0.25h |\n52: | 4.3.5 | Read annotation: `sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]` | Annotation key constant used | 0.25h |\n53: | 4.3.6 | Handle missing/empty annotation: return `ctrl.Result{}, nil` | No requeue for missing annotation | 0.25h |\n54: | 4.3.7 | Parse RFC3339 timestamp with `time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)` | Parsing logic implemented | 0.5h |\n55: | 4.3.8 | Handle parse error: return `ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err` | Parse error requeues with 30s | 0.5h |\n56: | 4.3.9 | Compute `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)` | Expiration calculation correct | 0.25h |\n57: | 4.3.10 | Check expiration: `if time.Now().After(expirationTime)` | Time comparison correct | 0.25h |\n58: | 4.3.11 | Delete expired sandbox: `r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)` | Delete call implemented | 0.5h |\n59: | 4.3.12 | Handle delete `IsNotFound`: return `ctrl.Result{}, nil` | Idempotent delete handling | 0.25h |\n60: | 4.3.13 | Handle other delete errors: return `ctrl.Result{}, err` | Other delete errors returned | 0.25h |\n61: | 4.3.14 | Requeue for future expiration: `ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}` | Future requeue logic correct | 0.5h |\n62: | 4.3.15 | Return empty result when delete succeeds | `return ctrl.Result{}, nil` | 0.25h |\n63: \n64: **Deliverable:** Reconcile method fully implements idle cleanup algorithm per delta-spec.\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## ST-4.4 — SetupWithManager Implementation\n69: \n70: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n71: |---|------|--------------|------|\n72: | 4.4.1 | Implement `SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error` method | Method signature correct | 0.25h |\n73: | 4.4.2 | Create controller: `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{})` | Builder pattern correct | 0.5h |\n74: | 4.4.3 | Complete controller: `.Complete(r)` | Controller completes with reconciler | 0.25h |\n75: | 4.4.4 | Return error from SetupWithManager | Error propagated correctly | 0.25h |\n76: \n77: **Deliverable:** Controller registration with manager works correctly.\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## ST-4.5 — Unit Tests — Reconcile Scenarios\n82: \n83: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n84: |---|------|--------------|------|\n85: | 4.5.1 | Create `pkg/agentd/reconciler_test.go` with build tag | File compiles with `go test` | 0.5h |\n86: | 4.5.2 | Write `TestReconcile_SandboxNotFound` — Get returns NotFound | Returns empty result, no error | 0.5h |\n87: | 4.5.3 | Write `TestReconcile_GetError` — Get returns other error | Returns error, no requeue | 0.5h |\n88: | 4.5.4 | Write `TestReconcile_NoAnnotation` — Sandbox without last-activity-time | Returns empty result, no delete | 0.5h |\n89: | 4.5.5 | Write `TestReconcile_EmptyAnnotation` — Empty annotation value | Returns empty result, no delete | 0.5h |\n90: | 4.5.6 | Write `TestReconcile_InvalidTimestamp` — Malformed RFC3339 | Returns RequeueAfter: 30s, with error | 0.5h |\n91: | 4.5.7 | Write `TestReconcile_NotExpired` — Last activity 5 minutes ago | Returns RequeueAfter: ~10m, no delete | 0.5h |\n92: | 4.5.8 | Write `TestReconcile_JustExpired` — Last activity exactly 15 minutes ago | Delete called, returns empty result | 0.5h |\n93: | 4.5.9 | Write `TestReconcile_Expired` — Last activity 20 minutes ago | Delete called, returns empty result | 0.5h |\n94: | 4.5.10 | Write `TestReconcile_DeleteNotFound` — Delete returns NotFound | Returns empty result, no error | 0.5h |\n95: | 4.5.11 | Write `TestReconcile_DeleteError` — Delete returns other error | Returns error for retry | 0.5h |\n96: | 4.5.12 | Write `TestReconcile_FutureExpirationRequeue` — Verify RequeueAfter calculation | RequeueAfter matches time.Until | 0.5h |\n97: \n98: **Deliverable:** All reconcile scenario tests pass with >85% coverage.\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## ST-4.6 — Unit Tests — Mock Client Setup\n103: \n104: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n105: |---|------|--------------|------|\n106: | 4.6.1 | Create mock client implementing `client.Client` interface | Mock compiles | 0.5h |\n107: | 4.6.2 | Implement mock `Get` method with configurable return values | Returns configured Sandbox/error | 0.5h |\n108: | 4.6.3 | Implement mock `Delete` method with configurable return values | Returns configured error | 0.5h |\n109: | 4.6.4 | Create test helpers for building Sandbox objects with annotations | Helper functions work | 0.5h |\n110: | 4.6.5 | Create test helpers for timestamp generation (past, future, RFC3339) | Time helpers accurate | 0.5h |\n111: \n112: **Deliverable:** Mock infrastructure supports all reconciler tests.\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## ST-4.7 — Binary Entry Point (cmd/agentd)\n117: \n118: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n119: |---|------|--------------|------|\n120: | 4.7.1 | Create `cmd/agentd/` directory structure | Directory exists | 0.25h |\n121: | 4.7.2 | Create `cmd/agentd/main.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n122: | 4.7.3 | Import required packages (controller-runtime, sandbox types, core k8s) | All imports resolve | 0.5h |\n123: | 4.7.4 | Initialize scheme builder: `schemeBuilder := runtime.NewSchemeBuilder()` | Scheme builder created | 0.25h |\n124: | 4.7.5 | Register core Kubernetes scheme: `utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))` | Core types registered | 0.5h |\n125: | 4.7.6 | Register Sandbox scheme: `utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))` | Sandbox types registered | 0.5h |\n126: | 4.7.7 | Create manager: `ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{...})` | Manager created with options | 0.5h |\n127: | 4.7.8 | Configure manager scheme: `Scheme: schemeBuilder` | Scheme passed to manager | 0.25h |\n128: | 4.7.9 | Disable metrics: `Metrics: metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"}` | Metrics disabled | 0.25h |\n129: | 4.7.10 | Disable health probes: `HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"` | Health probes disabled | 0.25h |\n130: | 4.7.11 | Create reconciler: `&agentd.Reconciler{Client: mgr.GetClient(), Scheme: mgr.GetScheme()}` | Reconciler initialized | 0.5h |\n131: | 4.7.12 | Setup controller: `reconciler.SetupWithManager(mgr)` | Controller registered | 0.5h |\n132: | 4.7.13 | Start manager: `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())` | Manager starts with signal handler | 0.5h |\n133: | 4.7.14 | Handle manager start errors | Errors logged and process exits | 0.25h |\n134: \n135: **Deliverable:** Binary compiles and can be started (integration tests verify full functionality).\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## ST-4.8 — Documentation\n140: \n141: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n142: |---|------|--------------|------|\n143: | 4.8.1 | Add package-level GoDoc for `pkg/agentd` | Overview documentation complete | 0.5h |\n144: | 4.8.2 | Document `Reconciler` struct with inline comments | Purpose and fields documented | 0.25h |\n145: | 4.8.3 | Document `Reconcile` method with algorithm description | Algorithm steps documented | 0.5h |\n146: | 4.8.4 | Document `SetupWithManager` method | Purpose and usage documented | 0.25h |\n147: | 4.8.5 | Add code comments for non-trivial logic in Reconcile | Inline comments explain decisions | 0.5h |\n148: | 4.8.6 | Document constants (`SessionExpirationTimeout`, `RequeueAfterParseError`) | Constants explained | 0.25h |\n149: | 4.8.7 | Add README or doc.go explaining how to run agentd | Usage documentation | 0.5h |\n150: \n151: **Deliverable:** Code is well-documented with GoDoc.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## ST-4.9 — Build and Integration Verification\n156: \n157: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n158: |---|------|--------------|------|\n159: | 4.9.1 | Verify `go build ./pkg/agentd/...` succeeds | Package builds without errors | 0.25h |\n160: | 4.9.2 | Verify `go build ./cmd/agentd/...` succeeds | Binary builds without errors | 0.25h |\n161: | 4.9.3 | Run unit tests: `go test ./pkg/agentd/... -v` | All tests pass | 0.5h |\n162: | 4.9.4 | Run tests with coverage: `go test ./pkg/agentd/... -cover` | Coverage >85% | 0.25h |\n163: | 4.9.5 | Run race detector: `go test ./pkg/agentd/... -race` | No race conditions detected | 0.5h |\n164: | 4.9.6 | Run go vet: `go vet ./pkg/agentd/...` | No issues reported | 0.25h |\n165: \n166: **Deliverable:** All build and quality checks pass.\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Summary\n171: \n172: | Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n173: |-------|-------|------------|\n174: | ST-4.1: Package Structure | 5 | 1.75h |\n175: | ST-4.2: Reconciler Struct | 4 | 1.25h |\n176: | ST-4.3: Reconcile Method | 15 | 5.5h |\n177: | ST-4.4: SetupWithManager | 4 | 1.25h |\n178: | ST-4.5: Unit Tests (Scenarios) | 12 | 6h |\n179: | ST-4.6: Unit Tests (Mock Setup) | 5 | 2.5h |\n180: | ST-4.7: Binary Entry Point | 14 | 6h |\n181: | ST-4.8: Documentation | 7 | 3h |\n182: | ST-4.9: Build Verification | 6 | 2.5h |\n183: | **Total** | **72** | **30.75h** |\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## File Deliverables Checklist\n188: \n189: - [ ] `pkg/agentd/reconciler.go` — Reconciler implementation\n190: - [ ] `pkg/agentd/reconciler_test.go` — Unit tests for reconciler\n191: - [ ] `cmd/agentd/main.go` — Binary entry point\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## Verification Commands\n196: \n197: ```bash\n198: # Build verification\n199: make build\n200: # OR:\n201: go build ./pkg/agentd/...\n202: go build ./cmd/agentd/...\n203: \n204: # Unit tests\n205: go test ./pkg/agentd/... -v\n206: \n207: # With coverage\n208: go test ./pkg/agentd/... -cover\n209: \n210: # Race detection\n211: go test ./pkg/agentd/... -race\n212: \n213: # Static analysis\n214: go vet ./pkg/agentd/...\n215: \n216: # Binary build\n217: go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n218: \n219: # Run binary (requires k8s config)\n220: ./bin/agentd\n221: ```\n222: \n223: ---\n224: \n225: ## Definition of Done\n226: \n227: - [ ] All 72 tasks complete\n228: - [ ] Reconciler implements full idle cleanup algorithm per delta-spec\n229: - [ ] SetupWithManager registers controller correctly\n230: - [ ] Unit tests pass (>85% coverage)\n231: - [ ] All scenario tests from delta-spec pass\n232: - [ ] Race detector clean\n233: - [ ] `go build ./pkg/agentd/...` succeeds\n234: - [ ] `go build ./cmd/agentd/...` succeeds\n235: - [ ] Documentation complete with GoDoc\n236: - [ ] Binary starts successfully (integration test)\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## Dependencies\n241: \n242: | Dependency | Purpose |\n243: |------------|---------|\n244: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller-runtime framework |\n245: | `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1` | Sandbox CRD types |\n246: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | Kubernetes API errors |\n247: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | Kubernetes runtime types |\n248: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/scheme` | Core Kubernetes scheme |\n249: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` | Annotation key constants |\n250: \n251: ---\n252: \n253: ## Design Notes\n254: \n255: - **Timeout:** 15 minutes hardcoded (`SessionExpirationTimeout`)\n256: - **Parse error retry:** 30 seconds (`RequeueAfterParseError`)\n257: - **Annotation key:** Uses `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` constant\n258: - **Timestamp format:** RFC3339 (e.g., \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\")\n259: - **Idempotency:** NotFound errors on Get/Delete treated as success\n260: - **Future requeue:** Uses `time.Until(expirationTime)` for precise scheduling\n261: - **Metrics:** Disabled (BindAddress: \"0\")\n262: - **Health probes:** Disabled (HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\")\n263: - **Signal handling:** Uses `ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()` for graceful shutdown\n264: \n265: ---\n266: \n267: ## Algorithm Reference (from delta-spec)\n268: \n269: ```\n270: 1. Get Sandbox by NamespacedName\n271: 2. If IsNotFound(err) → return (Result{}, nil)\n272: 3. If other get error → return (Result{}, err)\n273: 4. Read last-activity-time annotation\n274: 5. If missing/empty → return (Result{}, nil)\n275: 6. Parse RFC3339 timestamp\n276: 7. If parse error → return (Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)\n277: 8. Compute expirationTime = lastActivity + 15 minutes\n278: 9. If time.Now().After(expirationTime):\n279:    - Delete Sandbox\n280:    - If delete NotFound → return (Result{}, nil)\n281:    - If delete error → return (Result{}, err)\n282:    - Else → return (Result{}, nil)\n283: 10. Else → return (Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil)\n284: ```\n\n(End of file - total 284 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 (Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** S  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n> **Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md), idle-cleanup/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-018 implements the Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller that watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). The controller uses controller-runtime for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Package Structure and Constants\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775881544384,"end":1775881544426}}}}
