{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775881553299,"sessionID":"ses_2853666dbffeDUJW2TNchl5Tol","part":{"id":"prt_d7aca0592001EU5sQKPyzR1e10","messageID":"msg_d7ac9fdfe001umJORsLWeiY0Ir","sessionID":"ses_2853666dbffeDUJW2TNchl5Tol","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881560328,"sessionID":"ses_2853666dbffeDUJW2TNchl5Tol","part":{"id":"prt_d7aca118c001z77cXUx5wwk4Yo","messageID":"msg_d7ac9fdfe001umJORsLWeiY0Ir","sessionID":"ses_2853666dbffeDUJW2TNchl5Tol","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018 Design: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-018  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S (Small)\n9: \n10: The Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller is a Kubernetes controller that automatically deletes AgentRuntime resources that have exceeded their configured idle timeout. It monitors the `LastActivityTime` field in AgentRuntime status and compares it against the `IdleTimeoutSeconds` specified in the spec to determine when a resource should be cleaned up.\n11: \n12: This implementation integrates with:\n13: - **AgentRuntime API (pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1)**: Watches AgentRuntime resources\n14: - **client-go library**: Uses generated Kubernetes clientset for API interactions\n15: - **controller-runtime**: Manages the controller lifecycle and reconciliation loop\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Architecture\n20: \n21: ### High-Level Design\n22: \n23: ```\n24: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                         Kubernetes Cluster                                   │\n26: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n27: │  │                         AgentRuntime Resources                          │  │\n28: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                    │  │\n29: │  │  │  Runtime 1  │  │  Runtime 2  │  │  Runtime N  │                    │  │\n30: │  │  │ (active)    │  │ (idle 20m)  │  │ (idle 45m)  │                    │  │\n31: │  │  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                    │  │\n32: │  │         │                │                │                            │  │\n33: │  │         │                ▼                ▼                            │  │\n34: │  │         │         ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐                  │  │\n35: │  │         │         │ Timeout: 15m │  │ Timeout: 30m │                  │  │\n36: │  │         │         │ DELETE       │  │ DELETE       │                  │  │\n37: │  │         │         └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘                  │  │\n38: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n39: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n40: │                      Agentd Controller (Idle Cleanup)                        │\n41: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n42: │  │                      Reconciliation Loop                                │  │\n43: │  │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌───────────┐  │  │\n44: │  │  │    Get      │──►│   Check     │──►│  Calculate  │──►│  Delete   │  │  │\n45: │  │  │   AgentRun  │   │ IdleTimeout │   │  Remaining  │   │  if Idle  │  │  │\n46: │  │  │   time      │   │   Config    │   │   Time      │   │  Timeout  │  │  │\n47: │  │  └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └───────────┘  │  │\n48: │  │         │                │                │                │          │  │\n49: │  │         ▼                ▼                ▼                ▼          │  │\n50: │  │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n51: │  │  │                    Requeue Decision                              │  │  │\n52: │  │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐              │  │  │\n53: │  │  │  │  No Timeout │  │   Idle      │  │   Error     │              │  │  │\n54: │  │  │  │  Configured │  │   Detected  │  │   Occurred  │              │  │  │\n55: │  │  │  │  ──► Skip   │  │  ──► Delete │  │  ──► Requeue│              │  │  │\n56: │  │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘              │  │  │\n57: │  │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n58: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n59: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n60: │                      Client-Go Integration Layer                             │\n61: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │\n62: │  │  AgentRuntime    │  │  Typed Client    │  │  Status Subresource      │   │\n63: │  │  Interface       │  │  (v1alpha1)      │  │  (Get/Update)            │   │\n64: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │\n65: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n66: ```\n67: \n68: ### Component Architecture\n69: \n70: ```\n71: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n72: │                     Idle Cleanup Controller Flow                             │\n73: │                                                                              │\n74: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n75: │  │  Watch   │──►│  Reconcile│──►│   Get    │──►│  Parse   │──►│  Check   │  │\n76: │  │  Events  │   │  Request  │   │  AgentRun │   │  Timeout │   │  Activity│  │\n77: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   │  time     │   │  Config  │   │  Time    │  │\n78: │                                └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n79: │                                                                     │        │\n80: │                          ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n81: │                          │                                                   │\n82: │                          ▼                                                   │\n83: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n84: │  │  Return  │◀──│  Schedule│◀──│  Delete  │◀──│  Expired │◀──│Calculate │  │\n85: │  │  Result  │   │  Requeue │   │  Resource│   │  ?       │   │Idle Time │  │\n86: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n87: │                                                                              │\n88: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n89: ```\n90: \n91: ### Component Interactions\n92: \n93: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n94: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n95: | **Reconciler** | Core reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime | context.Context, reconcile.Request | reconcile.Result, error |\n96: | **AgentRuntimeInterface** | Typed client for AgentRuntime CRUD | AgentRuntime objects | AgentRuntime operations |\n97: | **IdleTimeoutChecker** | Determines if resource has exceeded idle timeout | AgentRuntime status | bool (expired), time.Duration (remaining) |\n98: | **CleanupExecutor** | Performs the deletion of expired resources | AgentRuntime reference | error |\n99: | **RequeueCalculator** | Calculates next requeue time | remaining duration | reconcile.Result |\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## Directory Structure\n104: \n105: ```\n106: pkg/agentd/\n107: ├── controller.go         # Main reconciler implementation (~180 lines)\n108: ├── controller_test.go    # Unit tests for reconciler (~200 lines)\n109: ├── config.go             # Controller configuration (~80 lines)\n110: ├── metrics.go            # Prometheus metrics for cleanup operations (~60 lines)\n111: └── doc.go                # Package documentation (~20 lines)\n112: \n113: cmd/agentd/\n114: └── main.go               # Controller entry point (~100 lines)\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## Data Structures\n120: \n121: ### Domain Types\n122: \n123: #### Reconciler\n124: \n125: ```go\n126: // Reconciler reconciles AgentRuntime objects for idle cleanup.\n127: type Reconciler struct {\n128:     // Client is the Kubernetes client for AgentRuntime resources\n129:     client client.Client\n130:     \n131:     // Scheme is the runtime scheme for type registration\n132:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n133:     \n134:     // Clock provides time functionality (allows mocking in tests)\n135:     Clock Clock\n136:     \n137:     // Metrics collects operational metrics\n138:     Metrics *Metrics\n139: }\n140: \n141: // Clock abstracts time operations for testability.\n142: type Clock interface {\n143:     Now() time.Time\n144: }\n145: \n146: // realClock implements Clock using the system clock.\n147: type realClock struct{}\n148: \n149: func (c *realClock) Now() time.Time {\n150:     return time.Now()\n151: }\n152: \n153: // NewReconciler creates a new AgentRuntime idle cleanup reconciler.\n154: func NewReconciler(client client.Client, scheme *runtime.Scheme) *Reconciler {\n155:     return &Reconciler{\n156:         Client:  client,\n157:         Scheme:  scheme,\n158:         Clock:   &realClock{},\n159:         Metrics: newMetrics(),\n160:     }\n161: }\n162: ```\n163: \n164: #### IdleTimeoutConfig\n165: \n166: ```go\n167: // IdleTimeoutConfig holds the idle timeout configuration.\n168: type IdleTimeoutConfig struct {\n169:     // DefaultTimeout is the fallback timeout when not specified in spec\n170:     DefaultTimeout time.Duration\n171:     \n172:     // MaxTimeout is the maximum allowed idle timeout\n173:     MaxTimeout time.Duration\n174:     \n175:     // MinTimeout is the minimum allowed idle timeout\n176:     MinTimeout time.Duration\n177: }\n178: \n179: // DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig returns the default configuration.\n180: func DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig() IdleTimeoutConfig {\n181:     return IdleTimeoutConfig{\n182:         DefaultTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n183:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n184:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n185:     }\n186: }\n187: \n188: // Validate checks if the configuration is valid.\n189: func (c *IdleTimeoutConfig) Validate() error {\n190:     if c.DefaultTimeout < c.MinTimeout {\n191:         return fmt.Errorf(\"default timeout %v is less than minimum %v\", \n192:             c.DefaultTimeout, c.MinTimeout)\n193:     }\n194:     if c.DefaultTimeout > c.MaxTimeout {\n195:         return fmt.Errorf(\"default timeout %v is greater than maximum %v\",\n196:             c.DefaultTimeout, c.MaxTimeout)\n197:     }\n198:     return nil\n199: }\n200: ```\n201: \n202: #### CleanupResult\n203: \n204: ```go\n205: // CleanupResult represents the outcome of a cleanup check.\n206: type CleanupResult struct {\n207:     // ShouldDelete indicates whether the resource should be deleted\n208:     ShouldDelete bool\n209:     \n210:     // Reason provides a human-readable explanation\n211:     Reason string\n212:     \n213:     // IdleDuration is how long the resource has been idle\n214:     IdleDuration time.Duration\n215:     \n216:     // TimeoutDuration is the configured timeout\n217:     TimeoutDuration time.Duration\n218:     \n219:     // RemainingTime is time until cleanup (zero if ShouldDelete)\n220:     RemainingTime time.Duration\n221: }\n222: \n223: // String returns a string representation of the result.\n224: func (r *CleanupResult) String() string {\n225:     if r.ShouldDelete {\n226:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"cleanup: %s (idle %v, timeout %v)\", \n227:             r.Reason, r.IdleDuration, r.TimeoutDuration)\n228:     }\n229:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"skip: %s (idle %v, remaining %v)\",\n230:         r.Reason, r.IdleDuration, r.RemainingTime)\n231: }\n232: ```\n233: \n234: ### Request/Response Types\n235: \n236: #### ReconcileRequest (Internal)\n237: \n238: ```go\n239: // ReconcileRequest wraps controller-runtime's reconcile.Request.\n240: type ReconcileRequest struct {\n241:     // NamespacedName identifies the AgentRuntime resource\n242:     NamespacedName types.NamespacedName\n243: }\n244: \n245: // ToControllerRuntime converts to controller-runtime request.\n246: func (r *ReconcileRequest) ToControllerRuntime() reconcile.Request {\n247:     return reconcile.Request{NamespacedName: r.NamespacedName}\n248: }\n249: ```\n250: \n251: ### Internal Types\n252: \n253: #### ControllerConfig\n254: \n255: ```go\n256: // ControllerConfig contains environment-based configuration.\n257: type ControllerConfig struct {\n258:     // LeaderElection enables leader election for HA\n259:     LeaderElection bool\n260:     \n261:     // SyncPeriod is the period for full re-listing of resources\n262:     SyncPeriod time.Duration\n263:     \n264:     // WorkerCount is the number of concurrent reconcile workers\n265:     WorkerCount int\n266:     \n267:     // IdleTimeout is the default idle timeout configuration\n268:     IdleTimeout IdleTimeoutConfig\n269:     \n270:     // MetricsBindAddress is the address for metrics server (\":8080\" or \"0\" to disable)\n271:     MetricsBindAddress string\n272:     \n273:     // HealthProbeBindAddress is the address for health probes (\":8081\" or \"0\" to disable)\n274:     HealthProbeBindAddress string\n275: }\n276: \n277: // LoadConfig loads configuration from environment variables.\n278: func LoadConfig() (*ControllerConfig, error) {\n279:     cfg := &ControllerConfig{\n280:         LeaderElection:         getEnvBool(\"AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION\", true),\n281:         SyncPeriod:             getEnvDuration(\"AGENTD_SYNC_PERIOD\", 10*time.Minute),\n282:         WorkerCount:            getEnvInt(\"AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT\", 1),\n283:         IdleTimeout:            DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig(),\n284:         MetricsBindAddress:     getEnvOrDefault(\"AGENTD_METRICS_BIND_ADDRESS\", \"0\"),\n285:         HealthProbeBindAddress: getEnvOrDefault(\"AGENTD_HEALTH_PROBE_BIND_ADDRESS\", \"0\"),\n286:     }\n287:     \n288:     // Override idle timeout from env if specified\n289:     if timeout := os.Getenv(\"AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT\"); timeout != \"\" {\n290:         if d, err := time.ParseDuration(timeout); err == nil {\n291:             cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout = d\n292:         } else {\n293:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT: %v\", err)\n294:         }\n295:     }\n296:     \n297:     if err := cfg.IdleTimeout.Validate(); err != nil {\n298:         return nil, err\n299:     }\n300:     \n301:     return cfg, nil\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: #### Metrics\n306: \n307: ```go\n308: // Metrics holds Prometheus metrics for the controller.\n309: type Metrics struct {\n310:     // ReconcileTotal is the total number of reconciliations\n311:     ReconcileTotal prometheus.Counter\n312:     \n313:     // ReconcileErrors is the total number of reconciliation errors\n314:     ReconcileErrors prometheus.Counter\n315:     \n316:     // CleanupTotal is the total number of successful cleanups\n317:     CleanupTotal prometheus.Counter\n318:     \n319:     // CleanupDuration is the duration of cleanup operations\n320:     CleanupDuration prometheus.Histogram\n321:     \n322:     // IdleDuration is the idle duration of cleaned resources\n323:     IdleDuration prometheus.Histogram\n324: }\n325: \n326: // newMetrics creates a new Metrics instance.\n327: func newMetrics() *Metrics {\n328:     return &Metrics{\n329:         ReconcileTotal: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n330:             Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_reconcile_total\",\n331:             Help: \"Total number of idle cleanup reconciliations\",\n332:         }),\n333:         ReconcileErrors: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n334:             Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_reconcile_errors_total\",\n335:             Help: \"Total number of idle cleanup reconciliation errors\",\n336:         }),\n337:         CleanupTotal: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n338:             Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_total\",\n339:             Help: \"Total number of idle cleanups performed\",\n340:         }),\n341:         CleanupDuration: prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n342:             Name:    \"agentd_idle_cleanup_duration_seconds\",\n343:             Help:    \"Duration of idle cleanup operations\",\n344:             Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n345:         }),\n346:         IdleDuration: prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n347:             Name:    \"agentd_idle_cleanup_idle_duration_seconds\",\n348:             Help:    \"Idle duration of cleaned resources\",\n349:             Buckets: []float64{60, 300, 600, 1800, 3600, 7200, 86400},\n350:         }),\n351:     }\n352: }\n353: \n354: // Register registers metrics with the provided registry.\n355: func (m *Metrics) Register(reg prometheus.Registerer) error {\n356:     collectors := []prometheus.Collector{\n357:         m.ReconcileTotal,\n358:         m.ReconcileErrors,\n359:         m.CleanupTotal,\n360:         m.CleanupDuration,\n361:         m.IdleDuration,\n362:     }\n363:     for _, c := range collectors {\n364:         if err := reg.Register(c); err != nil {\n365:             return err\n366:         }\n367:     }\n368:     return nil\n369: }\n370: ```\n371: \n372: ### Constants\n373: \n374: ```go\n375: // Default configuration values\n376: const (\n377:     // DefaultIdleTimeout is the default idle timeout when not specified\n378:     DefaultIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n379:     \n380:     // DefaultRequeueInterval is the default interval for requeuing when error occurs\n381:     DefaultRequeueInterval = 30 * time.Second\n382:     \n383:     // MinRequeueInterval is the minimum requeue interval\n384:     MinRequeueInterval = 5 * time.Second\n385: )\n386: \n387: // Error reasons for status updates\n388: const (\n389:     // ReasonIdleTimeout indicates cleanup due to idle timeout\n390:     ReasonIdleTimeout = \"IdleTimeoutExceeded\"\n391:     \n392:     // ReasonNoIdleConfig indicates no idle timeout configured\n393:     ReasonNoIdleConfig = \"NoIdleTimeoutConfigured\"\n394:     \n395:     // ReasonActive indicates resource is still active\n396:     ReasonActive = \"ResourceStillActive\"\n397: )\n398: \n399: // Event types\n400: const (\n401:     // EventTypeNormal indicates a normal event\n402:     EventTypeNormal = \"Normal\"\n403:     \n404:     // EventTypeWarning indicates a warning event\n405:     EventTypeWarning = \"Warning\"\n406: )\n407: \n408: // Event reasons\n409: const (\n410:     // EventReasonIdleCleanup indicates successful idle cleanup\n411:     EventReasonIdleCleanup = \"IdleCleanup\"\n412:     \n413:     // EventReasonCleanupFailed indicates failed cleanup\n414:     EventReasonCleanupFailed = \"CleanupFailed\"\n415: )\n416: ```\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ## API Contracts\n421: \n422: ### Reconciler Interface\n423: \n424: ```go\n425: // ReconcilerInterface defines the interface for AgentRuntime reconciliation.\n426: type ReconcilerInterface interface {\n427:     // Reconcile performs idle cleanup reconciliation for the given AgentRuntime.\n428:     //\n429:     // Parameters:\n430:     //   - ctx: Context for cancellation and timeouts\n431:     //   - req: Reconcile request containing the AgentRuntime namespaced name\n432:     //\n433:     // Returns:\n434:     //   - reconcile.Result: Indicates whether to requeue and when\n435:     //   - error: Non-nil if reconciliation failed (triggers requeue with backoff)\n436:     //\n437:     // Behavior:\n438:     //   1. Fetch AgentRuntime from Kubernetes API\n439:     //   2. Check if IdleTimeoutSeconds is configured in spec\n440:     //   3. Parse LastActivityTime from status\n441:     //   4. Calculate idle duration\n442:     //   5. If idle duration > timeout, delete the resource\n443:     //   6. Otherwise, requeue after remaining time\n444:     Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)\n445: }\n446: \n447: // SetupWithManager sets up the reconciler with the controller manager.\n448: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n449:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n450:         For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).\n451:         WithEventFilter(predicate.GenerationChangedPredicate{}).\n452:         Complete(r)\n453: }\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ### Idle Timeout Checker\n457: \n458: ```go\n459: // CheckIdleTimeout determines if an AgentRuntime has exceeded its idle timeout.\n460: //\n461: // Parameters:\n462: //   - agentRuntime: The AgentRuntime to check\n463: //   - now: Current time\n464: //\n465: // Returns:\n466: //   - *CleanupResult: Result indicating whether cleanup should occur\n467: //   - error: If status fields cannot be parsed\n468: //\n469: // Logic:\n470: //   1. If IdleTimeoutSeconds is nil/0, return ShouldDelete=false (no timeout configured)\n471: //   2. If LastActivityTime is nil, use creation timestamp\n472: //   3. Calculate idleDuration = now - lastActivityTime\n473: //   4. timeoutDuration = IdleTimeoutSeconds converted to time.Duration\n474: //   5. If idleDuration >= timeoutDuration, return ShouldDelete=true\n475: //   6. Otherwise, return ShouldDelete=false with RemainingTime = timeoutDuration - idleDuration\n476: func CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, now time.Time) (*CleanupResult, error)\n477: ```\n478: \n479: ### Cleanup Executor\n480: \n481: ```go\n482: // ExecuteCleanup deletes an AgentRuntime that has exceeded its idle timeout.\n483: //\n484: // Parameters:\n485: //   - ctx: Context for the delete operation\n486: //   - client: Kubernetes client\n487: //   - agentRuntime: The AgentRuntime to delete\n488: //\n489: // Returns:\n490: //   - error: nil if deletion initiated successfully, otherwise error\n491: //\n492: // Notes:\n493: //   - Uses foreground deletion for graceful cleanup\n494: //   - Sets deletion reason annotation before deletion\n495: func ExecuteCleanup(ctx context.Context, client client.Client, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) error\n496: ```\n497: \n498: ### Configuration Functions\n499: \n500: ```go\n501: // LoadConfig loads controller configuration from environment variables.\n502: //\n503: // Required: None (all have defaults)\n504: //\n505: // Optional environment variables:\n506: //   - AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION: Enable leader election (default: \"true\")\n507: //   - AGENTD_SYNC_PERIOD: Full re-list period (default: \"10m\")\n508: //   - AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT: Concurrent workers (default: \"1\")\n509: //   - AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT: Default idle timeout (default: \"15m\")\n510: //   - AGENTD_METRICS_BIND_ADDRESS: Metrics server address (default: \"0\")\n511: //   - AGENTD_HEALTH_PROBE_BIND_ADDRESS: Health probe address (default: \"0\")\n512: //\n513: // Returns:\n514: //   - *ControllerConfig: Loaded configuration\n515: //   - error: If configuration is invalid\n516: func LoadConfig() (*ControllerConfig, error)\n517: \n518: // GetTimeoutDuration extracts timeout duration from AgentRuntime spec.\n519: //\n520: // Returns:\n521: //   - time.Duration: The idle timeout duration\n522: //   - bool: true if timeout is configured, false otherwise\n523: func GetTimeoutDuration(spec *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec, defaults IdleTimeoutConfig) (time.Duration, bool)\n524: ```\n525: \n526: ### Metrics Functions\n527: \n528: ```go\n529: // RecordReconcile records a reconciliation attempt.\n530: func (m *Metrics) RecordReconcile()\n531: \n532: // RecordReconcileError records a reconciliation error.\n533: func (m *Metrics) RecordReconcileError()\n534: \n535: // RecordCleanup records a successful cleanup.\n536: func (m *Metrics) RecordCleanup(duration time.Duration, idleDuration time.Duration)\n537: ```\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Error Handling\n542: \n543: ### Error Categories and Codes\n544: \n545: | Error | Code | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n546: |-------|------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n547: | `ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound` | `NOT_FOUND` | AgentRuntime was deleted | No | Return success (no requeue) |\n548: | `ErrGetAgentRuntimeFailed` | `GET_FAILED` | Failed to fetch AgentRuntime | Yes | Requeue with backoff |\n549: | `ErrParseLastActivity` | `PARSE_FAILED` | Failed to parse LastActivityTime | No | Log and skip resource |\n550: | `ErrDeleteFailed` | `DELETE_FAILED` | Deletion API call failed | Yes | Requeue with backoff |\n551: | `ErrInvalidTimeout` | `INVALID_TIMEOUT` | IdleTimeoutSeconds invalid | No | Log and skip resource |\n552: \n553: ### Sentinel Errors\n554: \n555: ```go\n556: // Controller errors\n557: var (\n558:     ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound = errors.New(\"agentruntime: resource not found\")\n559:     ErrGetAgentRuntimeFailed = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to get resource\")\n560:     ErrParseLastActivity = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to parse last activity time\")\n561:     ErrDeleteFailed = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to delete resource\")\n562:     ErrInvalidTimeout = errors.New(\"agentruntime: invalid idle timeout configuration\")\n563: )\n564: ```\n565: \n566: ### Error Structures\n567: \n568: ```go\n569: // ReconcileError represents a reconciliation error with context.\n570: type ReconcileError struct {\n571:     // Code is the machine-readable error code\n572:     Code string `json:\"code\"`\n573:     \n574:     // Message is the human-readable error message\n575:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n576:     \n577:     // Resource is the namespaced name of the affected resource\n578:     Resource types.NamespacedName `json:\"resource\"`\n579:     \n580:     // Retryable indicates if the error is retryable\n581:     Retryable bool `json:\"retryable\"`\n582:     \n583:     // underlying is the wrapped error\n584:     underlying error\n585: }\n586: \n587: // Error returns the error string.\n588: func (e *ReconcileError) Error() string {\n589:     if e.underlying != nil {\n590:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (resource: %s): %v\", \n591:             e.Code, e.Message, e.Resource, e.underlying)\n592:     }\n593:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (resource: %s)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Resource)\n594: }\n595: \n596: // Unwrap returns the wrapped error.\n597: func (e *ReconcileError) Unwrap() error {\n598:     return e.underlying\n599: }\n600: \n601: // IsRetryable returns true if the error is retryable.\n602: func (e *ReconcileError) IsRetryable() bool {\n603:     return e.Retryable\n604: }\n605: \n606: // NewReconcileError creates a new ReconcileError.\n607: func NewReconcileError(code, message string, resource types.NamespacedName, retryable bool, underlying error) *ReconcileError {\n608:     return &ReconcileError{\n609:         Code:       code,\n610:         Message:    message,\n611:         Resource:   resource,\n612:         Retryable:  retryable,\n613:         underlying: underlying,\n614:     }\n615: }\n616: ```\n617: \n618: ### Error Handling Patterns\n619: \n620: #### Reconcile Error Handling\n621: \n622: ```go\n623: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error) {\n624:     r.Metrics.RecordReconcile()\n625:     \n626:     log := log.FromContext(ctx).WithValues(\"agentruntime\", req.NamespacedName)\n627:     \n628:     // Fetch AgentRuntime\n629:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n630:     if err := r.client.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, agentRuntime); err != nil {\n631:         if errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n632:             log.Info(\"AgentRuntime not found, skipping\")\n633:             return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n634:         }\n635:         r.Metrics.RecordReconcileError()\n636:         return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n637:             \"GET_FAILED\",\n638:             \"failed to get AgentRuntime\",\n639:             req.NamespacedName,\n640:             true,\n641:             err,\n642:         )\n643:     }\n644:     \n645:     // Check idle timeout\n646:     result, err := r.checkAndCleanup(ctx, agentRuntime)\n647:     if err != nil {\n648:         r.Metrics.RecordReconcileError()\n649:         reconcileErr, ok := err.(*ReconcileError)\n650:         if ok && !reconcileErr.IsRetryable() {\n651:             log.Error(err, \"Non-retryable error during cleanup, skipping\")\n652:             return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n653:         }\n654:         return reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: DefaultRequeueInterval}, err\n655:     }\n656:     \n657:     return result, nil\n658: }\n659: ```\n660: \n661: #### Check and Cleanup Pattern\n662: \n663: ```go\n664: func (r *Reconciler) checkAndCleanup(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (reconcile.Result, error) {\n665:     log := log.FromContext(ctx)\n666:     \n667:     // Check idle timeout\n668:     cleanupResult, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, r.Clock.Now())\n669:     if err != nil {\n670:         return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n671:             \"PARSE_FAILED\",\n672:             \"failed to check idle timeout\",\n673:             types.NamespacedName{Name: agentRuntime.Name, Namespace: agentRuntime.Namespace},\n674:             false,\n675:             err,\n676:         )\n677:     }\n678:     \n679:     log.V(1).Info(\"Idle check result\", \"result\", cleanupResult.String())\n680:     \n681:     // If should delete, execute cleanup\n682:     if cleanupResult.ShouldDelete {\n683:         start := r.Clock.Now()\n684:         if err := ExecuteCleanup(ctx, r.client, agentRuntime); err != nil {\n685:             return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n686:                 \"DELETE_FAILED\",\n687:                 \"failed to delete idle AgentRuntime\",\n688:                 types.NamespacedName{Name: agentRuntime.Name, Namespace: agentRuntime.Namespace},\n689:                 true,\n690:                 err,\n691:             )\n692:         }\n693:         \n694:         duration := r.Clock.Now().Sub(start)\n695:         r.Metrics.RecordCleanup(duration, cleanupResult.IdleDuration)\n696:         log.Info(\"Deleted idle AgentRuntime\",\n697:             \"idleDuration\", cleanupResult.IdleDuration,\n698:             \"timeoutDuration\", cleanupResult.TimeoutDuration)\n699:         \n700:         return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n701:     }\n702:     \n703:     // Requeue after remaining time\n704:     if cleanupResult.RemainingTime > 0 {\n705:         // Add small buffer to avoid race conditions\n706:         requeueAfter := cleanupResult.RemainingTime + MinRequeueInterval\n707:         log.V(1).Info(\"Requeuing for next idle check\",\n708:             \"requeueAfter\", requeueAfter,\n709:             \"remainingTime\", cleanupResult.RemainingTime)\n710:         return reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: requeueAfter}, nil\n711:     }\n712:     \n713:     return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n714: }\n715: ```\n716: \n717: ---\n718: \n719: ## Testing Strategy\n720: \n721: ### Unit Tests\n722: \n723: #### controller_test.go\n724: \n725: ```go\n726: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_NotFound(t *testing.T) {\n727:     // Setup\n728:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().Build()\n729:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n730:     \n731:     // Execute - resource doesn't exist\n732:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n733:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n734:     })\n735:     \n736:     // Assert\n737:     require.NoError(t, err)\n738:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n739:     assert.Equal(t, time.Duration(0), result.RequeueAfter)\n740: }\n741: \n742: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_NoIdleTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n743:     // Setup - AgentRuntime without idle timeout\n744:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n745:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n746:             Name:      \"test\",\n747:             Namespace: \"default\",\n748:         },\n749:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n750:             // IdleTimeoutSeconds not set\n751:         },\n752:     }\n753:     \n754:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n755:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n756:     \n757:     // Execute\n758:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n759:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n760:     })\n761:     \n762:     // Assert - should not requeue, no timeout configured\n763:     require.NoError(t, err)\n764:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n765:     \n766:     // Verify resource still exists\n767:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n768:     require.NoError(t, err)\n769: }\n770: \n771: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_IdleTimeoutNotExpired(t *testing.T) {\n772:     // Setup\n773:     now := time.Now()\n774:     lastActivity := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-5 * time.Minute)) // 5 minutes ago\n775:     \n776:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n777:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n778:             Name:      \"test\",\n779:             Namespace: \"default\",\n780:         },\n781:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n782:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n783:         },\n784:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n785:             LastActivityTime: &lastActivity,\n786:         },\n787:     }\n788:     \n789:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n790:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n791:     reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n792:     \n793:     // Execute\n794:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n795:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n796:     })\n797:     \n798:     // Assert - should requeue after ~10 minutes\n799:     require.NoError(t, err)\n800:     assert.InDelta(t, 10*time.Minute, result.RequeueAfter, float64(time.Minute))\n801:     \n802:     // Verify resource still exists\n803:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n804:     require.NoError(t, err)\n805: }\n806: \n807: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_IdleTimeoutExpired(t *testing.T) {\n808:     // Setup\n809:     now := time.Now()\n810:     lastActivity := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-30 * time.Minute)) // 30 minutes ago\n811:     \n812:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n813:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n814:             Name:      \"test\",\n815:             Namespace: \"default\",\n816:         },\n817:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n818:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n819:         },\n820:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n821:             LastActivityTime: &lastActivity,\n822:         },\n823:     }\n824:     \n825:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n826:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n827:     reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n828:     \n829:     // Execute\n830:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n831:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n832:     })\n833:     \n834:     // Assert - should not requeue, resource deleted\n835:     require.NoError(t, err)\n836:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n837:     \n838:     // Verify resource deleted\n839:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n840:     require.Error(t, err)\n841:     assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n842: }\n843: \n844: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_NoLastActivityTime(t *testing.T) {\n845:     // Setup - no LastActivityTime, should use creation time\n846:     now := time.Now()\n847:     creationTime := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-20 * time.Minute))\n848:     \n849:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n850:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n851:             Name:              \"test\",\n852:             Namespace:         \"default\",\n853:             CreationTimestamp: creationTime,\n854:         },\n855:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n856:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n857:         },\n858:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n859:             // LastActivityTime not set\n860:         },\n861:     }\n862:     \n863:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n864:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n865:     reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n866:     \n867:     // Execute\n868:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n869:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n870:     })\n871:     \n872:     // Assert - should delete based on creation time\n873:     require.NoError(t, err)\n874:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n875:     \n876:     // Verify resource deleted\n877:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n878:     require.Error(t, err)\n879:     assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n880: }\n881: \n882: func TestCheckIdleTimeout_NoTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n883:     now := time.Now()\n884:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n885:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n886:             // IdleTimeoutSeconds not set\n887:         },\n888:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n889:             LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-1 * time.Hour)},\n890:         },\n891:     }\n892:     \n893:     result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n894:     require.NoError(t, err)\n895:     assert.False(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n896:     assert.Equal(t, \"no idle timeout configured\", result.Reason)\n897: }\n898: \n899: func TestCheckIdleTimeout_NotExpired(t *testing.T) {\n900:     now := time.Now()\n901:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n902:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n903:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](1800), // 30 minutes\n904:         },\n905:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n906:             LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-10 * time.Minute)},\n907:         },\n908:     }\n909:     \n910:     result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n911:     require.NoError(t, err)\n912:     assert.False(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n913:     assert.InDelta(t, 20*time.Minute, result.RemainingTime, float64(time.Second))\n914: }\n915: \n916: func TestCheckIdleTimeout_Expired(t *testing.T) {\n917:     now := time.Now()\n918:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n919:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n920:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](600), // 10 minutes\n921:         },\n922:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n923:             LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-15 * time.Minute)},\n924:         },\n925:     }\n926:     \n927:     result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n928:     require.NoError(t, err)\n929:     assert.True(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n930:     assert.Equal(t, \"idle timeout exceeded\", result.Reason)\n931:     assert.InDelta(t, 15*time.Minute, result.IdleDuration, float64(time.Second))\n932: }\n933: \n934: // fakeClock implements Clock for testing\n935: type fakeClock struct {\n936:     now time.Time\n937: }\n938: \n939: func (c *fakeClock) Now() time.Time {\n940:     return c.now\n941: }\n942: ```\n943: \n944: #### config_test.go\n945: \n946: ```go\n947: func TestLoadConfig_Defaults(t *testing.T) {\n948:     cfg, err := LoadConfig()\n949:     require.NoError(t, err)\n950:     \n951:     assert.True(t, cfg.LeaderElection)\n952:     assert.Equal(t, 10*time.Minute, cfg.SyncPeriod)\n953:     assert.Equal(t, 1, cfg.WorkerCount)\n954:     assert.Equal(t, 15*time.Minute, cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout)\n955: }\n956: \n957: func TestLoadConfig_FromEnv(t *testing.T) {\n958:     t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT\", \"30m\")\n959:     t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT\", \"5\")\n960:     t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION\", \"false\")\n961:     \n962:     cfg, err := LoadConfig()\n963:     require.NoError(t, err)\n964:     \n965:     assert.Equal(t, 30*time.Minute, cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout)\n966:     assert.Equal(t, 5, cfg.WorkerCount)\n967:     assert.False(t, cfg.LeaderElection)\n968: }\n969: \n970: func TestIdleTimeoutConfig_Validate(t *testing.T) {\n971:     // Valid config\n972:     validConfig := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n973:         DefaultTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n974:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n975:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n976:     }\n977:     require.NoError(t, validConfig.Validate())\n978:     \n979:     // Invalid: default < min\n980:     invalidConfig1 := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n981:         DefaultTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n982:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n983:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n984:     }\n985:     require.Error(t, invalidConfig1.Validate())\n986:     \n987:     // Invalid: default > max\n988:     invalidConfig2 := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n989:         DefaultTimeout: 48 * time.Hour,\n990:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n991:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n992:     }\n993:     require.Error(t, invalidConfig2.Validate())\n994: }\n995: ```\n996: \n997: ### Integration Tests\n998: \n999: ```go\n1000: func TestIntegration_Controller(t *testing.T) {\n1001:     if testing.Short() {\n1002:         t.Skip(\"Skipping integration test\")\n1003:     }\n1004:     \n1005:     // Setup test environment\n1006:     cfg := &rest.Config{Host: os.Getenv(\"KUBECONFIG\")}\n1007:     scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n1008:     require.NoError(t, runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme))\n1009:     \n1010:     // Create manager\n1011:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(cfg, ctrl.Options{\n1012:         Scheme: scheme,\n1013:     })\n1014:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1015:     \n1016:     // Setup reconciler\n1017:     reconciler := NewReconciler(mgr.GetClient(), mgr.GetScheme())\n1018:     require.NoError(t, reconciler.SetupWithManager(mgr))\n1019:     \n1020:     // Create test AgentRuntime\n1021:     ctx := context.Background()\n1022:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n1023:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n1024:             Name:      \"test-idle-cleanup\",\n1025:             Namespace: \"default\",\n1026:         },\n1027:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n1028:             Image:              \"test:latest\",\n1029:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](60), // 1 minute\n1030:         },\n1031:     }\n1032:     \n1033:     err = mgr.GetClient().Create(ctx, agentRuntime)\n1034:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1035:     \n1036:     // Update status with old last activity time\n1037:     agentRuntime.Status.LastActivityTime = &metav1.Time{\n1038:         Time: time.Now().Add(-2 * time.Minute), // 2 minutes ago\n1039:     }\n1040:     err = mgr.GetClient().Status().Update(ctx, agentRuntime)\n1041:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1042:     \n1043:     // Trigger reconciliation\n1044:     _, err = reconciler.Reconcile(ctx, reconcile.Request{\n1045:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test-idle-cleanup\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n1046:     })\n1047:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1048:     \n1049:     // Verify deletion\n1050:     err = mgr.GetClient().Get(ctx, types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test-idle-cleanup\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n1051:     require.Error(t, err)\n1052:     assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n1053: }\n1054: ```\n1055: \n1056: ### Test Execution\n1057: \n1058: ```bash\n1059: # Run all controller tests\n1060: make test PKG=./pkg/agentd/...\n1061: \n1062: # Run with race detector\n1063: go test -race ./pkg/agentd/...\n1064: \n1065: # Run specific test categories\n1066: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestReconciler\"\n1067: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestCheckIdleTimeout\"\n1068: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestLoadConfig\"\n1069: \n1070: # With coverage\n1071: go test ./pkg/agentd/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n1072: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n1073: \n1074: # Integration tests (requires k8s cluster)\n1075: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -tags=integration\n1076: ```\n1077: \n1078: ---\n1079: \n1080: ## Security Considerations\n1081: \n1082: ### Resource Deletion\n1083: \n1084: - Deletion uses foreground propagation for graceful cleanup\n1085: - Only deletes resources in the same namespace the controller has access to\n1086: - RBAC rules must be carefully configured to allow only delete on AgentRuntime\n1087: - Audit logging should be enabled for deletion events\n1088: \n1089: ### RBAC Requirements\n1090: \n1091: ```yaml\n1092: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1093: kind: ClusterRole\n1094: metadata:\n1095:   name: agentd-idle-cleanup\n1096: rules:\n1097: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1098:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n1099:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n1100: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1101:   resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n1102:   verbs: [\"get\"]\n1103: ```\n1104: \n1105: ### Time Safety\n1106: \n1107: - Clock skew between controller and API server is handled via configurable tolerance\n1108: - Time comparisons use monotonic clocks where available\n1109: - Leap seconds are handled gracefully\n1110: \n1111: ### Logging Safety\n1112: \n1113: - Resource names and namespaces are logged at appropriate levels\n1114: - No sensitive data (tokens, credentials) is logged\n1115: - Log levels: DEBUG (V(2)) for timing details, INFO for deletions, WARN for errors\n1116: \n1117: ---\n1118: \n1119: ## Performance Considerations\n1120: \n1121: ### Scalability\n1122: \n1123: | Metric | Target | Notes |\n1124: |--------|--------|-------|\n1125: | Reconcile latency | < 100ms | P99 for single resource |\n1126: | Concurrent reconciles | 10+ | Configurable via worker count |\n1127: | Memory per resource | < 1KB | Minimal resource footprint |\n1128: | API calls per reconcile | 1-2 | Get + optional Delete |\n1129: \n1130: ### Optimization Strategies\n1131: \n1132: - Single API call per reconcile (Get only, Delete only when needed)\n1133: - Precise requeue timing based on remaining idle time\n1134: - No polling - event-driven reconciliation\n1135: - Minimal memory allocation in hot path\n1136: - Shared informer cache for reduced API server load\n1137: \n1138: ### Resource Usage\n1139: \n1140: - **Memory**: Scales with number of AgentRuntimes being watched\n1141: - **CPU**: Low baseline, spikes during bulk reconciliations\n1142: - **Network**: Minimal - only API calls for Get and Delete\n1143: - **Storage**: None (no persistent storage)\n1144: \n1145: ---\n1146: \n1147: ## Integration Points\n1148: \n1149: ### With AgentRuntime API\n1150: \n1151: ```go\n1152: // Watches AgentRuntime resources via controller-runtime\n1153: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n1154:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n1155:         For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).\n1156:         WithEventFilter(predicate.GenerationChangedPredicate{}).\n1157:         Complete(r)\n1158: }\n1159: ```\n1160: \n1161: ### With client-go\n1162: \n1163: ```go\n1164: // Uses generated client for typed operations\n1165: import runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n1166: \n1167: // Get AgentRuntime using controller-runtime client (wrapper around client-go)\n1168: err := r.client.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, agentRuntime)\n1169: ```\n1170: \n1171: ### With Workload Manager\n1172: \n1173: The controller reads `LastActivityTime` which is updated by the workload manager:\n1174: \n1175: ```go\n1176: // LastActivityTime is set by workload manager when processing requests\n1177: lastActivity := agentRuntime.Status.LastActivityTime\n1178: ```\n1179: \n1180: ### With Metrics Server\n1181: \n1182: ```go\n1183: // Metrics are exposed for Prometheus scraping\n1184: metrics.Registry.MustRegister(reconciler.Metrics.ReconcileTotal)\n1185: metrics.Registry.MustRegister(reconciler.Metrics.CleanupTotal)\n1186: ```\n1187: \n1188: ---\n1189: \n1190: ## Dependencies\n1191: \n1192: ```go\n1193: import (\n1194:     \"context\"\n1195:     \"errors\"\n1196:     \"fmt\"\n1197:     \"os\"\n1198:     \"time\"\n1199:     \n1200:     \"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n1201:     corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n1202:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n1203:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n1204:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n1205:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n1206:     \"k8s.io/utils/ptr\"\n1207:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n1208:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/log\"\n1209:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager\"\n1210:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/reconcile\"\n1211:     \n1212:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n1213: )\n1214: ```\n1215: \n1216: | Package | Purpose | Version |\n1217: |---------|---------|---------|\n1218: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller framework | v0.19.x |\n1219: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Metrics | v1.20.x |\n1220: | `k8s.io/api` | Kubernetes API types | v0.31.x |\n1221: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Kubernetes utilities | v0.31.x |\n1222: | `k8s.io/utils` | Kubernetes helpers | v0.0.x |\n1223: \n1224: ---\n1225: \n1226: ## References\n1227: \n1228: - [AgentRuntime Types](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go) — AgentRuntime CRD types\n1229: - [client-go Spec](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md) — client-go library specification\n1230: - [Idle Cleanup (Sandbox)](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli-benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md) — Related sandbox idle cleanup design\n1231: - [controller-runtime](https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime) — Controller runtime documentation\n1232: - [Kubernetes Controllers](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/controller/) — Kubernetes controller patterns\n1233: \n1234: ---\n1235: \n1236: *AR-018 — Module: pkg/agentd — Language: Go — Size: S*\n\n(End of file - total 1236 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018 Design: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-018  \n**Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S (Small)\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller is a Kubernetes controller that automatically deletes AgentRuntime resources that have exceeded their configured idle timeout. It monitors the `LastActivityTime` field in AgentRuntime status and compares it against the `IdleTimeoutSeconds` specified in the spec to determine when a resource should be cleaned up.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **AgentRuntime API (pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1)**: Watches AgentRuntime resources\n- **client-go library**: Uses generated Kubernetes clientset for API interactions\n- **controller-runtime**: Manages the controller lifecycle and reconciliation loop\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775881560301,"end":1775881560324}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881560331,"sessionID":"ses_2853666dbffeDUJW2TNchl5Tol","part":{"id":"prt_d7aca176e001aCVy2EIrq62lHM","messageID":"msg_d7ac9fdfe001umJORsLWeiY0Ir","sessionID":"ses_2853666dbffeDUJW2TNchl5Tol","type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"toolu_functions.grep:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"archive|deferred|completed|done","path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018"},"output":"No files found","metadata":{"matches":0,"truncated":false},"title":"archive|deferred|completed|done","time":{"start":1775881560305,"end":1775881560330}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881560344,"sessionID":"ses_2853666dbffeDUJW2TNchl5Tol","part":{"id":"prt_d7aca085c001Q1Auw5P2FQ6Pi7","messageID":"msg_d7ac9fdfe001umJORsLWeiY0Ir","sessionID":"ses_2853666dbffeDUJW2TNchl5Tol","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-018\n6: **Module:** `pkg/agentd`\n7: **Language:** Go\n8: **Size:** S\n9: **Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md)\n10: \n11: The Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). It uses the controller-runtime framework for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Reconciliation Trigger\n18: \n19: The system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager's API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n22: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n23: - **AND** the agentd manager is running\n24: - **WHEN** the controller-runtime detects the change\n25: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function SHALL be invoked with the object's namespace and name\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Sandbox deletion triggers reconcile\n28: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is deleted from the cluster\n29: - **AND** the agentd manager is running\n30: - **WHEN** the controller-runtime detects the deletion\n31: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function SHALL be invoked to handle cleanup\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### Requirement: Idle Detection Input\n36: \n37: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue.\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n40: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` exists without the `last-activity-time` annotation\n41: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n42: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL NOT be deleted\n43: - **AND** the result SHALL have zero `RequeueAfter`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Empty annotation value means no deletion\n46: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` exists with `last-activity-time` annotation set to empty string\n47: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n48: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL NOT be deleted\n49: - **AND** the result SHALL have zero `RequeueAfter`\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Idle Detection Parsing\n54: \n55: When the annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `RequeueAfter: 30 seconds` and the parse error.\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Valid RFC3339 timestamp parses successfully\n58: - **GIVEN** annotation value is a valid RFC3339 timestamp (e.g., \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\")\n59: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` is called\n60: - **THEN** the timestamp SHALL be parsed successfully\n61: - **AND** reconciliation SHALL proceed to expiration check\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Invalid timestamp requeues with error\n64: - **GIVEN** annotation value is not a valid RFC3339 timestamp (e.g., \"invalid-time\")\n65: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n66: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n67: - **AND** the error SHALL be logged\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Malformed timestamp requeues\n70: - **GIVEN** annotation value is malformed (e.g., \"2024-13-45T99:99:99Z\")\n71: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n72: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ### Requirement: Expiration Threshold\n77: \n78: The system SHALL define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`. The system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL delete the `Sandbox` resource.\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Idle beyond 15 minutes triggers delete\n81: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to a time more than 15 minutes in the past\n82: - **AND** `expirationTime = lastActivity + 15 minutes`\n83: - **AND** `time.Now()` is after `expirationTime`\n84: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n85: - **THEN** the controller SHALL call delete on the `Sandbox` resource\n86: - **AND** on success, reconcile SHALL return empty result with nil error\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Not yet expired requeues until expiration\n89: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is recent enough that expiration is in the future\n90: - **AND** `expirationTime = lastActivity + 15 minutes`\n91: - **AND** `time.Now()` is before `expirationTime`\n92: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n93: - **THEN** the result SHALL be `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)`\n94: - **AND** no delete SHALL occur\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Exactly at expiration triggers delete\n97: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is exactly 15 minutes ago\n98: - **AND** `time.Now()` equals `expirationTime`\n99: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n100: - **THEN** the controller SHALL call delete on the `Sandbox` resource\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Delete Idempotency\n105: \n106: When delete returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and SHALL return empty result with nil error. Other delete errors SHALL be returned to trigger retry.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Already deleted sandbox handled gracefully\n109: - **GIVEN** the API server returns `NotFound` on delete\n110: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n111: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n112: - **AND** no error SHALL be logged\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Delete conflict returns error for retry\n115: - **GIVEN** the API server returns a conflict error on delete\n116: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n117: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, err)`\n118: - **AND** controller-runtime SHALL retry with backoff\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Delete network error returns error for retry\n121: - **GIVEN** the API server returns a connection error on delete\n122: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n123: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, err)`\n124: - **AND** controller-runtime SHALL retry with backoff\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ### Requirement: Get Not Found Handling\n129: \n130: When get returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL return empty result and nil error.\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Sandbox removed before reconcile\n133: - **GIVEN** the sandbox no longer exists when Get is called\n134: - **AND** the API server returns `NotFound`\n135: - **WHEN** `Get` fails with not found\n136: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` without error\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ### Requirement: Manager Configuration\n141: \n142: The `agentd` binary SHALL construct controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`, SHALL disable metrics server (`BindAddress: \"0\"`), and SHALL disable health probe server (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Manager starts with correct configuration\n145: - **GIVEN** the scheme contains core Kubernetes types\n146: - **AND** the scheme contains `sandboxv1alpha1` types\n147: - **AND** metrics server is disabled\n148: - **AND** health probe server is disabled\n149: - **WHEN** the manager is created\n150: - **THEN** the manager SHALL start without error\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Signal-driven shutdown\n153: - **GIVEN** the process runs `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())`\n154: - **WHEN** SIGTERM or SIGINT is received\n155: - **THEN** the manager SHALL stop gracefully per controller-runtime defaults\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ## Changes to Base Specification\n160: \n161: This AR implements the Agentd idle cleanup controller using the client-go library interfaces defined in deployment/client-go.md. No modifications to existing interfaces.\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## New Interfaces\n166: \n167: ### Reconciler Interface\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: package agentd\n171: \n172: import (\n173:     \"context\"\n174:     \"time\"\n175: \n176:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n177:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n178:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/controller/controllerutil\"\n179:     ctrl \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n180: )\n181: \n182: // SessionExpirationTimeout defines the idle timeout before sandbox deletion\n183: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n184: \n185: // Reconciler reconciles Sandbox objects for idle cleanup\n186: type Reconciler struct {\n187:     client.Client\n188:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n189: }\n190: \n191: // Reconcile implements the idle cleanup logic\n192: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n193: \n194: // SetupWithManager sets up the controller with the Manager\n195: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### Main Entry Point\n199: \n200: ```go\n201: // cmd/agentd/main.go\n202: \n203: // Scheme registration\n204: var schemeBuilder = runtime.NewSchemeBuilder()\n205: \n206: func init() {\n207:     utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n208:     utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n209: }\n210: \n211: // main creates and runs the controller-runtime manager\n212: func main()\n213: ```\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ## Modified Interfaces\n218: \n219: None. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n220: \n221: ---\n222: \n223: ## Behavioral Changes\n224: \n225: | Behavior | Before | After |\n226: |----------|--------|-------|\n227: | Sandbox lifecycle | No automatic cleanup | Automatic deletion after 15 min idle |\n228: | Resource tracking | No activity tracking | last-activity-time annotation read |\n229: | Reconciliation | N/A | Controller-runtime reconciler watches Sandboxes |\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ## Dependencies\n234: \n235: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n236: |------------|---------|---------|\n237: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.x | Controller-runtime framework |\n238: | `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1` | Local | Sandbox CRD types |\n239: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | v0.x | Kubernetes API errors |\n240: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | v0.x | Kubernetes runtime types |\n241: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` | Local | Annotation key constants |\n242: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated client (base spec) |\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ## File Index\n247: \n248: | Path | Purpose |\n249: |------|---------|\n250: | `pkg/agentd/reconciler.go` | Reconciler implementation with idle cleanup logic |\n251: | `pkg/agentd/reconciler_test.go` | Unit tests for reconciler |\n252: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Binary entry point and manager setup |\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ## Constants\n257: \n258: | Constant | Value | Description |\n259: |----------|-------|-------------|\n260: | `SessionExpirationTimeout` | `15 * time.Minute` | Idle timeout before sandbox deletion |\n261: | `RequeueAfterParseError` | `30 * time.Second` | Requeue delay when timestamp parse fails |\n262: \n263: ---\n264: \n265: ## Configuration\n266: \n267: ### Environment Variables\n268: \n269: None. The controller uses hardcoded constants for configuration.\n270: \n271: ### Annotations Read\n272: \n273: | Annotation Key | Source | Description |\n274: |---------------|--------|-------------|\n275: | `last-activity-time` | `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` | RFC3339 timestamp of last sandbox activity |\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## API Endpoints Summary\n280: \n281: This AR is a controller (reconciler) that watches Kubernetes resources; no new API endpoints are exposed.\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ## Watched Resources\n286: \n287: | API Group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n288: |-----------|---------|------|---------|\n289: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Create, Update, Delete |\n290: \n291: No explicit `Owns` or `Watches` — single primary resource `Sandbox`.\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## Migration Notes\n296: \n297: - Ensure `sandboxv1alpha1` scheme is registered before starting the manager\n298: - The workload manager must set `last-activity-time` annotation on Sandboxes for cleanup to function\n299: - Existing Sandboxes without the annotation will not be cleaned up\n300: - Deploy agentd binary alongside other agentcube components\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n305: \n306: 1. **Reconciliation**: Controller-runtime reconciler registered for Sandbox resources\n307: 2. **Annotation Reading**: Correctly reads `last-activity-time` annotation from Sandbox metadata\n308: 3. **Timestamp Parsing**: Parses RFC3339 timestamps; handles parse errors with 30s requeue\n309: 4. **Expiration Logic**: Correctly computes expiration time (lastActivity + 15 minutes)\n310: 5. **Idle Detection**: Deletes sandboxes idle for more than 15 minutes\n311: 6. **Future Requeue**: Requeues with appropriate delay when expiration is in the future\n312: 7. **Idempotency**: Handles NotFound errors gracefully (no error returned)\n313: 8. **Error Handling**: Returns errors for retry on transient failures\n314: 9. **Manager Setup**: Correctly configures controller-runtime manager with scheme\n315: 10. **Signal Handling**: Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n316: 11. **Unit Tests**: >85% coverage on reconciler logic\n\n(End of file - total 316 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-018\n**Module:** `pkg/agentd`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** S\n**Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md)\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). It uses the controller-runtime framework for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciliation Trigger\n\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager's API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775881560297,"end":1775881560340}}}}
